1
00:00:55,238 --> 00:00:55,972
(This drama is a work of fiction.)

2
00:00:55,972 --> 00:00:56,806
(All characters, organizations,
and events in this drama are fictitious.)

3
00:00:56,806 --> 00:00:57,607
(This drama complied
with production guidelines...)

4
00:00:57,607 --> 00:00:58,375
(for filming child actors and animals.)

5
00:01:12,302 --> 00:01:13,103
Sir, now.

6
00:01:13,103 --> 00:01:14,471
Hold on. Wait.

7
00:01:22,712 --> 00:01:23,780
Hey.

8
00:01:24,414 --> 00:01:25,916
I told you to wait.

9
00:01:36,927 --> 00:01:39,229
Curry smells good.

10
00:01:41,264 --> 00:01:42,098
What?

11
00:01:44,434 --> 00:01:47,270
Good grief. I told you not to do that.

12
00:01:49,239 --> 00:01:50,774
Where did Myo Jin go?

13
00:01:50,774 --> 00:01:51,975
It's about time to eat.

14
00:01:54,244 --> 00:01:55,879
Did she go fishing with Muljjeong again?

15
00:01:57,981 --> 00:02:00,283
It's always that Muljjeong.

16
00:02:01,918 --> 00:02:04,120
I'll go bring them back, so set out
one more set of spoon and chopsticks.

17
00:02:04,955 --> 00:02:06,923
You really shouldn't be like that.

18
00:02:09,659 --> 00:02:11,561
If you care so much about him,

19
00:02:11,795 --> 00:02:14,197
go eat out with him yourself
and just send our kid home.

20
00:02:14,598 --> 00:02:16,833
Stop letting an outsider
hang around the house.

21
00:02:16,833 --> 00:02:19,202
Outsider?

22
00:02:19,202 --> 00:02:20,770
Are you going to keep saying that?

23
00:02:20,770 --> 00:02:22,606
Is Muljjeongi a stranger to us?

24
00:02:23,039 --> 00:02:24,541
Of course, he's a stranger.

25
00:02:25,509 --> 00:02:27,878
He's not even blind
or missing his arms or legs,

26
00:02:28,612 --> 00:02:31,948
but he still can't earn his keep at
that age, so he's a good-for-nothing bum.

27
00:02:32,182 --> 00:02:33,884
He's a bad influence on our girl too.

28
00:02:34,351 --> 00:02:35,619
Have you already forgotten?

29
00:02:35,952 --> 00:02:37,654
When we first moved here,

30
00:02:37,654 --> 00:02:39,723
who stood up
to the whole neighborhood for us?

31
00:02:40,524 --> 00:02:42,459
From teaching us how to raise seedlings...

32
00:02:42,459 --> 00:02:43,827
to introducing us to clients.

33
00:02:44,461 --> 00:02:47,464
Who do you think
we owe our livelihood to now?

34
00:02:49,299 --> 00:02:50,934
Do you really not remember anymore?

35
00:02:56,039 --> 00:02:57,174
I'm going to bring them back.

36
00:03:04,047 --> 00:03:05,949
I'm so grateful I could cry.

37
00:03:05,949 --> 00:03:08,285
Really.

38
00:03:10,854 --> 00:03:12,956
You're really good at catching fish.

39
00:03:13,523 --> 00:03:14,858
Why can't I do it?

40
00:03:15,125 --> 00:03:16,960
I haven't caught a single one yet.

41
00:03:19,396 --> 00:03:20,664
Myo Jin.

42
00:03:21,765 --> 00:03:24,434
Why can't you catch fish?

43
00:03:25,035 --> 00:03:26,736
You said I keep rushing.

44
00:03:27,003 --> 00:03:28,305
That I don't wait patiently.

45
00:03:30,874 --> 00:03:33,009
Right. If you know what the problem is,

46
00:03:33,009 --> 00:03:34,678
then why do you still think
you can't catch them?

47
00:03:35,278 --> 00:03:36,880
Because fishing is hard.

48
00:03:37,113 --> 00:03:38,448
But I can catch other things well.

49
00:03:39,883 --> 00:03:40,717
Really?

50
00:03:42,219 --> 00:03:45,021
Then should we go catch something else?

51
00:03:45,856 --> 00:03:49,192
You said you're good at catching
everything else, so let's see.

52
00:03:54,164 --> 00:03:54,998
Myo Jin.

53
00:03:55,832 --> 00:03:59,302
Whether you're catching fish
or catching a wild boar,

54
00:03:59,302 --> 00:04:01,171
the method is the same.

55
00:04:01,872 --> 00:04:02,772
What is?

56
00:04:02,973 --> 00:04:04,708
The thing you want to catch.

57
00:04:05,642 --> 00:04:07,043
Think like that thing.

58
00:04:08,078 --> 00:04:09,679
When it'll get hungry,

59
00:04:10,447 --> 00:04:11,948
where you should wait,

60
00:04:11,948 --> 00:04:14,518
and what kind of bait to use.

61
00:04:16,453 --> 00:04:17,587
And then?

62
00:04:19,823 --> 00:04:21,525
You set a trap...

63
00:04:21,525 --> 00:04:22,592
and wait.

64
00:04:23,293 --> 00:04:26,296
The bait changes,
but the way you catch it is the same.

65
00:04:27,464 --> 00:04:28,331
Lastly,

66
00:04:29,599 --> 00:04:30,901
there's just one thing
you need to remember.

67
00:04:31,735 --> 00:04:34,371
Don't rush. Take it slow.

68
00:04:35,038 --> 00:04:35,972
That's right.

69
00:04:37,507 --> 00:04:39,309
Myo Jin, Muljjeong.

70
00:04:39,609 --> 00:04:41,044
Come on and eat.

71
00:04:41,678 --> 00:04:43,213
Your mom made curry.

72
00:04:43,580 --> 00:04:44,748
Come on, both of you.

73
00:04:45,315 --> 00:04:46,149
- Curry?
- Curry?

74
00:04:46,583 --> 00:04:47,484
Let's go.

75
00:04:53,790 --> 00:04:56,593
(Hunt)

76
00:04:57,694 --> 00:05:01,231
(NFS)

77
00:05:06,837 --> 00:05:10,173
You're pestering me
this early in the morning.

78
00:05:10,173 --> 00:05:11,241
Where's Detective Woo?

79
00:05:11,241 --> 00:05:13,076
He says he has something else
to take care of.

80
00:05:13,910 --> 00:05:16,112
He calls nonstop when he needs something,

81
00:05:16,112 --> 00:05:17,514
then disappears when it's time to show up.

82
00:05:18,448 --> 00:05:19,382
He's unusual.

83
00:05:21,618 --> 00:05:22,686
Did anything turn up?

84
00:05:24,354 --> 00:05:25,789
Not from our team yet.

85
00:05:26,289 --> 00:05:29,459
I went back over
Choi Hee Su's autopsy results first,

86
00:05:29,860 --> 00:05:31,094
and it's definitely homicide.

87
00:05:32,329 --> 00:05:33,663
Anyway, give it a little more time.

88
00:05:34,898 --> 00:05:37,467
Even at a fire scene,

89
00:05:37,834 --> 00:05:39,503
something always turns up.

90
00:05:40,604 --> 00:05:42,772
Now I'm curious who did it.

91
00:05:42,772 --> 00:05:45,709
Cases like this are rare
unless the killer is a real veteran.

92
00:05:47,210 --> 00:05:49,045
Could an ordinary person do it,

93
00:05:49,746 --> 00:05:51,515
if they were smart and meticulous?

94
00:05:52,949 --> 00:05:53,884
It's hard to say.

95
00:05:55,218 --> 00:05:56,052
Then again,

96
00:05:56,052 --> 00:05:57,587
when I get curious these days,

97
00:05:57,587 --> 00:05:59,623
I learn things through social media.

98
00:06:00,123 --> 00:06:01,324
Sometimes that's better.

99
00:06:05,162 --> 00:06:07,664
I heard they found
a woman's footprint at the scene.

100
00:06:08,031 --> 00:06:09,032
A woman's footprint?

101
00:06:11,735 --> 00:06:13,403
What's unusual is that it was barefoot.

102
00:06:13,770 --> 00:06:16,439
Judging by the shape and size,
it's definitely a woman's,

103
00:06:16,840 --> 00:06:18,441
and they said
there was blood mixed in too.

104
00:06:18,775 --> 00:06:19,676
Did you know?

105
00:06:20,377 --> 00:06:21,244
No.

106
00:06:21,678 --> 00:06:24,581
But how could a footprint
from back then be found only now?

107
00:06:25,615 --> 00:06:26,850
That doesn't make sense.

108
00:06:26,850 --> 00:06:29,853
Some idiot must've missed evidence
they collected at the time.

109
00:06:30,487 --> 00:06:32,589
That's what happens
when people do their jobs like that.

110
00:06:32,589 --> 00:06:35,192
No wonder they all had to write reports
and got warnings too.

111
00:06:35,826 --> 00:06:38,428
How do you miss evidence
that was properly submitted?

112
00:06:39,396 --> 00:06:40,330
Wait.

113
00:06:40,730 --> 00:06:42,966
The person in charge here said
there was a reason.

114
00:06:43,733 --> 00:06:45,168
Detective Kang, was it?

115
00:06:45,168 --> 00:06:47,838
That guy came here alone to the NFS...

116
00:06:47,838 --> 00:06:49,840
and submitted only that piece
of evidence separately.

117
00:06:49,840 --> 00:06:51,541
Do you know Detective Kang?

118
00:06:51,541 --> 00:06:52,609
I do.

119
00:06:52,609 --> 00:06:54,611
He came here himself? Alone?

120
00:06:54,611 --> 00:06:56,213
He did.

121
00:06:56,213 --> 00:06:58,114
He asked the person in charge here...

122
00:06:58,114 --> 00:07:00,417
if he knew anyone at their station.

123
00:07:00,417 --> 00:07:02,219
When they said no,

124
00:07:02,219 --> 00:07:04,154
Detective Kang said,
"Then that's fine," and handed it over.

125
00:07:05,956 --> 00:07:06,790
Anyway,

126
00:07:07,657 --> 00:07:09,559
since you're here,
go talk to the person in charge.

127
00:07:10,227 --> 00:07:11,461
Yes, thank you.

128
00:07:11,962 --> 00:07:12,896
All right.

129
00:07:16,633 --> 00:07:17,767
Detective Kang did that?

130
00:07:18,201 --> 00:07:20,370
That punk just pulled off another one.

131
00:07:21,037 --> 00:07:22,372
So you confirmed it too, right?

132
00:07:22,372 --> 00:07:23,173
Yes.

133
00:07:23,173 --> 00:07:25,542
I begged them to fax
only that part just now,

134
00:07:25,542 --> 00:07:26,443
so compare it.

135
00:07:26,443 --> 00:07:27,777
Okay. Good work.

136
00:07:38,321 --> 00:07:39,256
Let's see.

137
00:07:39,689 --> 00:07:40,724
(Personal Information)

138
00:07:41,892 --> 00:07:44,461
Height, 166.7cm.

139
00:07:44,461 --> 00:07:46,663
Okay, 165 cm.

140
00:07:46,663 --> 00:07:48,265
Foot size, 240 mm.

141
00:07:48,899 --> 00:07:50,100
Two hundred forty.

142
00:07:52,302 --> 00:07:53,270
Bingo.

143
00:07:54,738 --> 00:07:55,939
Thank you, Detective Kang.

144
00:07:56,807 --> 00:07:57,974
That guy.

145
00:08:11,054 --> 00:08:13,623
(Call, Myo Jin 17 calls)

146
00:08:19,696 --> 00:08:22,065
So the villa accident was a murder...

147
00:08:22,065 --> 00:08:23,934
disguised as a fire.

148
00:08:23,934 --> 00:08:26,703
Based on the wound location
and depth pattern,

149
00:08:27,471 --> 00:08:29,673
it was most likely a grudge killing.

150
00:08:36,546 --> 00:08:37,581
I told you clearly...

151
00:08:37,581 --> 00:08:39,616
that Ham Myo Jin is back to normal.

152
00:08:40,116 --> 00:08:42,452
But isn't it terrifying
that she's pretending she isn't?

153
00:08:42,452 --> 00:08:44,387
In her current condition,

154
00:08:45,021 --> 00:08:46,923
her memory could come back at any time.

155
00:08:48,124 --> 00:08:50,227
(Myo Jin)

156
00:08:50,427 --> 00:08:51,261
Myo Jin.

157
00:09:01,771 --> 00:09:03,373
Why haven't you been answering?

158
00:09:03,907 --> 00:09:04,908
Where are you right now?

159
00:09:05,308 --> 00:09:06,343
I have something to say.

160
00:09:07,677 --> 00:09:08,512
Okay.

161
00:09:08,879 --> 00:09:11,982
I'll be there soon,

162
00:09:11,982 --> 00:09:13,016
so we'll talk when I get there.

163
00:09:13,517 --> 00:09:15,318
You're at home, right?

164
00:09:15,318 --> 00:09:16,153
No.

165
00:09:17,988 --> 00:09:18,955
Then where are you?

166
00:09:20,257 --> 00:09:21,691
Somewhere you know too.

167
00:10:12,943 --> 00:10:14,478
You still don't know me?

168
00:10:15,645 --> 00:10:17,047
Do you really think...

169
00:10:17,747 --> 00:10:19,349
I'd ask you a favor for free?

170
00:10:19,783 --> 00:10:22,786
Why are you back here
making a fuss and annoying me?

171
00:10:23,186 --> 00:10:25,655
Listen properly first,

172
00:10:25,655 --> 00:10:27,824
then get angry or annoyed.

173
00:10:28,692 --> 00:10:30,227
Honestly, I call it a favor,

174
00:10:30,694 --> 00:10:32,395
but is this really something
I'm doing only for myself?

175
00:10:33,663 --> 00:10:35,465
Then are you okay...

176
00:10:35,465 --> 00:10:37,200
with what those two are doing?

177
00:10:37,534 --> 00:10:40,370
You eat expensive food
and really have nothing better to do?

178
00:10:41,705 --> 00:10:44,174
Unlike you, I don't care
about other people's business.

179
00:10:44,174 --> 00:10:45,408
Other people?

180
00:10:46,009 --> 00:10:48,345
Right. Sure, they're other people.

181
00:10:49,045 --> 00:10:50,947
Other people who ruined someone's life...

182
00:10:50,947 --> 00:10:52,816
and then lived happily
like nothing happened.

183
00:10:53,150 --> 00:10:54,184
Damn it.

184
00:10:54,718 --> 00:10:56,419
Honestly, the money you got back then...

185
00:10:57,087 --> 00:10:59,022
wouldn't even cover
that family's dog food.

186
00:10:59,623 --> 00:11:01,424
After all those years in prison,

187
00:11:02,092 --> 00:11:03,960
what kind of payment is this?

188
00:11:03,960 --> 00:11:05,428
It makes me mad just thinking about it.

189
00:11:06,229 --> 00:11:08,732
That dog-food money bought me this place.

190
00:11:09,599 --> 00:11:11,434
If it's heaven to me, that's enough.

191
00:11:11,434 --> 00:11:13,904
Anyone listening would think
you're some enlightened monk.

192
00:11:17,174 --> 00:11:19,376
Cut the crap and talk straight.

193
00:11:20,610 --> 00:11:21,778
Why on earth...

194
00:11:22,279 --> 00:11:24,447
are you so desperate to destroy that girl?

195
00:11:28,418 --> 00:11:29,386
Fine.

196
00:11:33,990 --> 00:11:35,592
Today, we put all our cards on the table,

197
00:11:36,259 --> 00:11:37,661
and after that, no more arguments.

198
00:11:37,894 --> 00:11:38,728
Okay?

199
00:11:40,664 --> 00:11:42,065
First, we grab Ham Myo Jin,

200
00:11:42,065 --> 00:11:44,000
that cocky little bitch, by the throat,

201
00:11:44,734 --> 00:11:47,070
and use her to shake down
that thief Ryu Jun Ho.

202
00:11:47,671 --> 00:11:48,705
I saw that bastard Ryu Jun Ho...

203
00:11:49,973 --> 00:11:52,075
nurse Ham Myo Jin,

204
00:11:52,275 --> 00:11:54,711
and he was absolutely crazy about her.

205
00:11:55,045 --> 00:11:56,546
Of course.

206
00:11:57,080 --> 00:12:00,417
So in the end, you want to squeeze
money out of Mono Group?

207
00:12:01,418 --> 00:12:02,652
Exactly.

208
00:12:02,652 --> 00:12:04,421
Now you're finally getting it.

209
00:12:04,421 --> 00:12:06,823
Do you think...

210
00:12:06,823 --> 00:12:07,924
he will dance to your threats...

211
00:12:08,391 --> 00:12:09,926
over a girl...

212
00:12:10,694 --> 00:12:13,697
when he's the next head of
a conglomerate worth hundreds of billions?

213
00:12:13,697 --> 00:12:15,365
This is why you're so frustrating.

214
00:12:16,099 --> 00:12:18,135
You really don't know anything.

215
00:12:19,669 --> 00:12:20,837
After Chairman Choi and his daughter...

216
00:12:21,605 --> 00:12:23,974
burned to death overnight,

217
00:12:24,741 --> 00:12:27,477
Ham Myo Jin and Ryu Jun Ho are together.
Why do you think that is?

218
00:12:29,446 --> 00:12:30,280
Look at you.

219
00:12:31,047 --> 00:12:32,415
You still haven't figured it out, right?

220
00:12:34,718 --> 00:12:36,520
What really happened...

221
00:12:37,287 --> 00:12:38,788
with the crime
you took the fall for back then.

222
00:12:39,823 --> 00:12:40,891
What are you talking about?

223
00:12:41,124 --> 00:12:42,726
It wasn't Chairman Choi.

224
00:12:43,927 --> 00:12:45,695
It was those two who did it.

225
00:12:46,296 --> 00:12:47,464
Those two?

226
00:13:05,382 --> 00:13:06,650
Fine, I'll explain everything.

227
00:13:06,650 --> 00:13:08,385
No, I don't need it.

228
00:13:10,353 --> 00:13:12,422
What you're thinking right now
and what you're going to say.

229
00:13:12,422 --> 00:13:14,090
I already know it all.

230
00:13:14,724 --> 00:13:15,592
Myo Jin.

231
00:13:15,892 --> 00:13:18,929
Can't we just look ahead?

232
00:13:21,097 --> 00:13:23,099
Let's just remember the fact...

233
00:13:23,834 --> 00:13:25,268
that we love each other.

234
00:13:25,802 --> 00:13:26,670
Okay?

235
00:13:27,938 --> 00:13:29,339
You said to me...

236
00:13:29,940 --> 00:13:32,242
that no matter what happens,
you'd stay by my side.

237
00:13:33,543 --> 00:13:34,544
If only the two of us were left...

238
00:13:34,544 --> 00:13:36,880
Think again about why I said that.

239
00:13:38,682 --> 00:13:40,350
The reason won't be what you think.

240
00:13:41,218 --> 00:13:43,119
It may be too hard to handle.

241
00:13:43,119 --> 00:13:43,954
No.

242
00:13:46,423 --> 00:13:47,257
I know.

243
00:13:47,691 --> 00:13:50,193
I know what you were
waiting for by my side.

244
00:13:50,760 --> 00:13:52,329
(Approached Choi Hee Su's fiancé,
Name Ryu Jun Ho)

245
00:13:52,329 --> 00:13:54,064
(Chairman Choi Young Ho supports
Ryu Jun Ho's business.)

246
00:13:54,064 --> 00:13:55,799
(Using Choi Hee Su and Ryu Jun Ho
to find out Chairman Choi's whereabouts)

247
00:13:55,799 --> 00:13:57,100
(Neither of them has noticed.)

248
00:14:00,303 --> 00:14:02,105
I looked into Chairman Choi Young Ho.

249
00:14:02,405 --> 00:14:03,373
That's a relief.

250
00:14:05,208 --> 00:14:06,076
Me...

251
00:14:06,710 --> 00:14:07,577
and Hee Su.

252
00:14:08,612 --> 00:14:09,779
We were just means to an end.

253
00:14:11,515 --> 00:14:13,783
Tools for you
to get to Chairman Choi Young Ho.

254
00:14:14,384 --> 00:14:17,087
Myo Jin must be really curious
about my dad.

255
00:14:17,988 --> 00:14:19,623
She talks about him every day.

256
00:14:22,325 --> 00:14:24,127
That has nothing to do...

257
00:14:24,895 --> 00:14:26,029
with the fact that we love each other.

258
00:14:27,130 --> 00:14:28,031
Impressive.

259
00:14:29,866 --> 00:14:31,434
The way you can say that so shamelessly,

260
00:14:31,434 --> 00:14:33,804
as if you did nothing wrong.

261
00:14:36,239 --> 00:14:37,107
No!

262
00:14:38,942 --> 00:14:41,611
I know what I did wrong.

263
00:14:41,611 --> 00:14:43,180
I won't run from it.

264
00:14:43,446 --> 00:14:44,681
I'll pay any price...

265
00:14:44,681 --> 00:14:46,416
until you're fully satisfied,

266
00:14:46,416 --> 00:14:47,517
as much as it takes.

267
00:14:53,123 --> 00:14:56,326
(Seoul Namyeong Police Station)

268
00:15:00,864 --> 00:15:01,731
Sir.

269
00:15:02,465 --> 00:15:03,934
The warrant for Ham Myo Jin
has been issued.

270
00:15:03,934 --> 00:15:05,202
Didn't you hear?

271
00:15:07,270 --> 00:15:08,505
Aren't you happy?

272
00:15:09,439 --> 00:15:11,141
We have solid evidence and a warrant.

273
00:15:11,374 --> 00:15:13,276
Let's say we arrest Ham Myo Jin.

274
00:15:13,777 --> 00:15:15,111
But what happens to Ryu Jun Ho?

275
00:15:16,313 --> 00:15:18,148
We still don't have
solid physical evidence.

276
00:15:18,715 --> 00:15:20,417
Yeah, that's the problem.

277
00:15:22,886 --> 00:15:23,954
That is...

278
00:15:25,455 --> 00:15:26,323
Detective Kang.

279
00:15:26,890 --> 00:15:27,791
Don't tell me...

280
00:15:28,558 --> 00:15:31,161
The hard drive
with the villa CCTV recordings...

281
00:15:31,828 --> 00:15:33,463
didn't burn up and disappear,

282
00:15:34,197 --> 00:15:35,565
but was removed beforehand.

283
00:15:37,100 --> 00:15:38,468
Removed? By whom?

284
00:15:38,468 --> 00:15:41,304
Of those four fancy people, two are dead,

285
00:15:42,139 --> 00:15:43,607
and only two are left, aren't they?

286
00:15:45,642 --> 00:15:46,476
Let's go.

287
00:15:46,843 --> 00:15:48,411
Where? Right now?

288
00:15:49,112 --> 00:15:51,448
He's watching us
like he can see the palm of his hand.

289
00:15:52,215 --> 00:15:53,817
If he thinks Ham Myo Jin is in danger,

290
00:15:54,651 --> 00:15:55,619
do you think he'll sit still?

291
00:15:56,153 --> 00:15:57,420
We don't have time. Come on!

292
00:15:57,888 --> 00:15:58,955
Sir.

293
00:16:01,858 --> 00:16:02,692
Fine.

294
00:16:05,095 --> 00:16:07,230
Before I met you,

295
00:16:08,165 --> 00:16:10,167
I'd never lived as myself.

296
00:16:12,002 --> 00:16:15,705
All that wealth and honor
the world envies...

297
00:16:17,140 --> 00:16:18,675
were given to me by those two people.

298
00:16:20,343 --> 00:16:22,212
But there was a condition.

299
00:16:25,415 --> 00:16:26,383
Obedience.

300
00:16:26,950 --> 00:16:27,951
You little punk.

301
00:16:28,652 --> 00:16:29,553
Dad.

302
00:16:34,891 --> 00:16:38,528
You should think things through
before you do anything.

303
00:16:39,029 --> 00:16:41,798
Do you want me to tell you
what's going on right now?

304
00:16:43,099 --> 00:16:44,000
I'm sorry.

305
00:16:48,839 --> 00:16:50,907
Your flight leaves at dawn tomorrow.

306
00:16:51,575 --> 00:16:53,743
Stay completely quiet...

307
00:16:54,177 --> 00:16:55,512
until I send someone.

308
00:17:04,421 --> 00:17:05,388
Good job.

309
00:17:07,958 --> 00:17:10,861
From now on too,
you're the one who protects Hee Su.

310
00:17:11,828 --> 00:17:14,097
But know your place.

311
00:17:14,965 --> 00:17:17,567
If you don't, I'll teach you.

312
00:17:31,681 --> 00:17:33,650
I wanted to get away.

313
00:17:33,650 --> 00:17:34,584
I really did.

314
00:17:37,621 --> 00:17:40,223
Even if I had to give back
everything I'd received,

315
00:17:40,490 --> 00:17:42,859
I wanted to run away from those two.

316
00:17:45,762 --> 00:17:46,863
Would that have been possible?

317
00:17:51,501 --> 00:17:52,335
Would it?

318
00:17:53,303 --> 00:17:54,905
You knew too.

319
00:17:54,905 --> 00:17:57,007
You knew, and still accepted me.

320
00:17:58,775 --> 00:17:59,609
That's right.

321
00:18:00,243 --> 00:18:02,412
Maybe, regardless of my revenge,

322
00:18:03,880 --> 00:18:06,783
I could have shared
the future you wanted...

323
00:18:09,085 --> 00:18:11,188
only if my memories hadn't returned,

324
00:18:11,822 --> 00:18:14,491
and I'd never learned the truth
until the end.

325
00:18:14,491 --> 00:18:15,292
Myo Jin.

326
00:18:15,292 --> 00:18:16,193
In this world,

327
00:18:16,193 --> 00:18:19,095
no matter how hard you try,
there are things you can never forget.

328
00:18:21,064 --> 00:18:22,566
Like my parents,

329
00:18:24,501 --> 00:18:25,902
whom you killed that day.

330
00:18:26,903 --> 00:18:28,638
No matter what I say,

331
00:18:29,773 --> 00:18:30,907
I know I can't undo that...

332
00:18:32,342 --> 00:18:34,678
or be forgiven.

333
00:18:35,245 --> 00:18:36,847
I'll spend my whole life atoning.

334
00:18:36,847 --> 00:18:38,248
Please give me a chance.

335
00:18:40,984 --> 00:18:41,852
Please.

336
00:18:43,286 --> 00:18:44,855
Don't look back.

337
00:18:44,855 --> 00:18:46,156
Let's just move forward.

338
00:18:47,991 --> 00:18:48,859
Give up.

339
00:18:50,760 --> 00:18:52,496
I'm no longer...

340
00:18:52,496 --> 00:18:54,664
the deranged patient you think I am.

341
00:18:57,400 --> 00:18:59,369
Do you really have to do this?

342
00:19:02,072 --> 00:19:03,140
Even if it means giving up...

343
00:19:06,209 --> 00:19:08,044
our entire future?

344
00:19:10,814 --> 00:19:12,649
I can't listen to this anymore.

345
00:19:13,016 --> 00:19:13,917
It's disgusting.

346
00:19:13,917 --> 00:19:15,485
Please, Myo Jin.

347
00:19:15,886 --> 00:19:16,720
Please.

348
00:19:18,955 --> 00:19:21,691
If this moment passes us by like this,

349
00:19:22,926 --> 00:19:24,861
you and I both...

350
00:19:29,900 --> 00:19:31,101
will regret it.

351
00:19:31,468 --> 00:19:33,303
You're going to pay.

352
00:19:34,671 --> 00:19:36,206
Because that recording
you heard earlier...

353
00:19:37,908 --> 00:19:40,076
will soon be heard by other people too.

354
00:20:02,799 --> 00:20:04,000
So this...

355
00:20:06,803 --> 00:20:08,104
was your idea of payback?

356
00:20:10,874 --> 00:20:11,942
Where is Ham Myo Jin?

357
00:20:11,942 --> 00:20:13,143
On the second floor.

358
00:20:15,345 --> 00:20:16,746
What is this?

359
00:20:20,417 --> 00:20:21,351
Wait.

360
00:20:21,751 --> 00:20:22,619
Ham Myo Jin.

361
00:20:24,087 --> 00:20:25,789
This is her room.

362
00:20:29,125 --> 00:20:30,093
What happened?

363
00:20:30,527 --> 00:20:32,128
She was definitely here.

364
00:20:32,963 --> 00:20:33,997
Hold on.

365
00:20:34,498 --> 00:20:35,298
Damn it.

366
00:20:57,587 --> 00:20:58,655
Atibam?

367
00:20:59,990 --> 00:21:02,058
Ryu Jun Ho isn't answering either.

368
00:21:02,058 --> 00:21:04,461
When they're together,
they usually don't pick up,

369
00:21:04,461 --> 00:21:06,129
so I think they're probably together.

370
00:21:07,964 --> 00:21:09,166
First, we grab Ham Myo Jin,

371
00:21:09,933 --> 00:21:11,902
that cocky little bitch, by the throat,

372
00:21:12,736 --> 00:21:15,071
and use her to shake down
that thief Ryu Jun Ho.

373
00:21:15,639 --> 00:21:16,640
I saw that bastard Ryu Jun Ho...

374
00:21:17,941 --> 00:21:20,277
nurse Ham Myo Jin,

375
00:21:20,277 --> 00:21:22,913
and he was absolutely crazy about her.

376
00:21:22,913 --> 00:21:24,314
Of course.

377
00:21:25,048 --> 00:21:28,518
So in the end, you want to squeeze
money out of Mono Group?

378
00:21:51,875 --> 00:21:53,610
This place has a nice atmosphere.

379
00:21:54,478 --> 00:21:56,413
You really do have good instincts.

380
00:21:58,849 --> 00:22:01,117
I don't care because
it's a neighborhood nobody notices,

381
00:22:02,152 --> 00:22:03,153
but will you be all right?

382
00:22:05,021 --> 00:22:05,922
What are you talking about?

383
00:22:06,323 --> 00:22:09,092
Are you saying you plan to kill today?

384
00:22:09,626 --> 00:22:11,695
No, that's not it.

385
00:22:12,095 --> 00:22:14,898
I'm saying they'll be able to trace
Ham Myo Jin coming all the way here later.

386
00:22:15,198 --> 00:22:16,333
What do we do about that?

387
00:22:16,700 --> 00:22:18,435
Look at the cat worrying about the mouse.

388
00:22:30,247 --> 00:22:32,983
But does Ham Myo Jin know this place?

389
00:22:33,984 --> 00:22:35,185
A place this empty and out of the way?

390
00:22:35,986 --> 00:22:38,655
Somehow, right after I got out of prison,

391
00:22:39,689 --> 00:22:42,192
she came here with a knife
in less than a week.

392
00:22:42,826 --> 00:22:43,927
Look here.

393
00:22:45,295 --> 00:22:46,530
She gave me this medal.

394
00:22:47,430 --> 00:22:48,765
Damn.

395
00:22:49,065 --> 00:22:51,434
I'm telling you,
that girl is vicious as hell.

396
00:22:52,202 --> 00:22:53,503
Just wait until the job's done.

397
00:22:53,904 --> 00:22:55,872
I'll bury her nice and neat
in a sunny spot.

398
00:22:57,841 --> 00:22:58,608
What?

399
00:23:04,347 --> 00:23:05,482
Is that Ham Myo Jin's car?

400
00:23:05,882 --> 00:23:06,917
Yeah, that's right.

401
00:23:07,717 --> 00:23:09,719
- Or not?
- Who else would come but her?

402
00:23:11,221 --> 00:23:13,089
She arrived right on time.

403
00:23:13,089 --> 00:23:14,357
Okay.

404
00:23:16,860 --> 00:23:18,028
When you go there,

405
00:23:18,862 --> 00:23:20,997
the two bastards
I mentioned will be there.

406
00:23:22,299 --> 00:23:24,768
I said I'd go after finishing work
at the construction site,

407
00:23:25,435 --> 00:23:26,570
so even if a truck shows up,

408
00:23:27,037 --> 00:23:28,472
they won't avoid it.

409
00:23:28,472 --> 00:23:30,240
You want me to ram them with my car?

410
00:23:30,774 --> 00:23:31,608
Yes.

411
00:23:32,876 --> 00:23:34,578
They're quick to catch on,

412
00:23:35,378 --> 00:23:36,880
so don't let your guard down.

413
00:23:37,781 --> 00:23:39,049
End it in one strike.

414
00:23:39,716 --> 00:23:40,584
Boss.

415
00:23:40,984 --> 00:23:42,652
I'm a marksman.

416
00:23:43,253 --> 00:23:44,387
You know me.

417
00:23:45,088 --> 00:23:46,089
How many guys
have vanished without a trace...

418
00:23:46,089 --> 00:23:48,859
after I set my sights on them?

419
00:23:49,893 --> 00:23:52,062
There's one more.

420
00:23:55,465 --> 00:23:58,235
When the job's done,
come straight to the shop.

421
00:23:58,235 --> 00:23:59,069
Got it?

422
00:24:02,372 --> 00:24:03,473
- Sir.
- Yeah?

423
00:24:03,840 --> 00:24:05,442
I'll stay around the back for now,

424
00:24:05,942 --> 00:24:08,411
so you just get Ham Myo Jin
to step out of the car.

425
00:24:08,411 --> 00:24:09,279
Got it?

426
00:24:12,282 --> 00:24:13,850
Just stay here. It's fine.

427
00:24:14,317 --> 00:24:16,219
She thinks she's meeting you alone.

428
00:24:18,421 --> 00:24:20,524
I told her I'd be with a guest.

429
00:24:21,057 --> 00:24:21,858
What?

430
00:24:22,492 --> 00:24:25,162
Come to think of it,
we really do have quite a bond.

431
00:24:26,496 --> 00:24:28,431
What are you suddenly talking about?

432
00:24:28,431 --> 00:24:30,200
I've lived my whole life like a dog,

433
00:24:30,767 --> 00:24:32,903
and now I even have a friend
to go to the afterlife with.

434
00:24:33,637 --> 00:24:36,072
What a luxury this is,
right at the end of a dead-end life.

435
00:24:43,046 --> 00:24:43,947
Damn it.

436
00:24:45,015 --> 00:24:46,483
- Let go of me.
- Come here.

437
00:24:46,483 --> 00:24:47,551
What are you doing? Are you crazy?

438
00:24:52,489 --> 00:24:53,356
Let me go.

439
00:24:54,491 --> 00:24:57,294
She's a kid whose life was ruined...

440
00:24:57,294 --> 00:24:59,095
because she was stupid enough
to be fooled by you.

441
00:24:59,095 --> 00:25:00,030
And yet,

442
00:25:00,997 --> 00:25:03,567
you want me to hand her over again
to a worm like you again?

443
00:25:04,468 --> 00:25:06,169
Why are you two fighting?

444
00:25:06,169 --> 00:25:08,104
You damn lowlifes.

445
00:25:17,214 --> 00:25:20,016
If you want to die,
die alone, you son of a bitch.

446
00:25:20,217 --> 00:25:21,785
For trash like us,

447
00:25:22,419 --> 00:25:23,587
this is only right.

448
00:25:39,169 --> 00:25:40,871
Damn it.

449
00:25:41,538 --> 00:25:43,006
Are we too late here too?

450
00:25:43,006 --> 00:25:45,175
What on earth is going on?

451
00:25:45,642 --> 00:25:46,476
Sir.

452
00:25:46,977 --> 00:25:48,512
Both their phones are turned off.

453
00:25:49,012 --> 00:25:50,313
They're definitely together.

454
00:25:51,681 --> 00:25:52,816
Damn it!

455
00:26:02,659 --> 00:26:03,827
Choi Hee Su.

456
00:26:10,934 --> 00:26:12,936
(Kutmin)

457
00:26:14,204 --> 00:26:15,071
Sir.

458
00:26:16,039 --> 00:26:17,340
Isn't this an anesthetic?

459
00:26:21,044 --> 00:26:23,013
(Kutmin)

460
00:26:23,013 --> 00:26:23,947
It is.

461
00:26:24,648 --> 00:26:26,449
A kutumin-based drug...

462
00:26:27,450 --> 00:26:28,718
used for general anesthesia.

463
00:26:30,153 --> 00:26:32,923
Atibam and Kutmin.

464
00:26:33,723 --> 00:26:35,792
Ham Myo Jin and Ryu Jun Ho are together,

465
00:26:35,792 --> 00:26:36,960
so why would they need
something like that?

466
00:27:41,158 --> 00:27:42,592
I always thought...

467
00:27:48,565 --> 00:27:51,935
that the fact you'd lost
all your memories meant,

468
00:27:53,170 --> 00:27:54,004
in the end,

469
00:27:55,705 --> 00:27:57,808
that you and I...

470
00:27:59,810 --> 00:28:01,978
were destined to be the only ones left.

471
00:28:03,580 --> 00:28:05,148
That's not...

472
00:28:06,449 --> 00:28:07,551
destiny.

473
00:28:10,520 --> 00:28:12,956
It's delusion.

474
00:28:20,197 --> 00:28:21,331
Is that so?

475
00:28:23,233 --> 00:28:24,734
When we first met,

476
00:28:30,173 --> 00:28:31,141
I felt...

477
00:28:32,509 --> 00:28:34,744
that you shared the same feelings...

478
00:28:37,214 --> 00:28:38,014
as I did.

479
00:28:38,014 --> 00:28:38,849
Of course,

480
00:28:40,917 --> 00:28:43,320
it was probably all part of your plan.

481
00:28:45,055 --> 00:28:46,890
That's when I made my mistake.

482
00:28:48,859 --> 00:28:49,759
That day,

483
00:28:52,662 --> 00:28:54,898
if I hadn't said those words...

484
00:28:57,033 --> 00:29:00,971
(The day before the accident)

485
00:29:15,352 --> 00:29:16,386
Jun Ho.

486
00:29:22,359 --> 00:29:23,193
Yeah?

487
00:29:25,095 --> 00:29:26,463
You should sleep some more.

488
00:29:26,863 --> 00:29:28,431
Do you have to go to the airport already?

489
00:29:32,102 --> 00:29:33,770
I'm about to head out.

490
00:29:41,812 --> 00:29:42,779
I'm scared.

491
00:29:44,648 --> 00:29:46,449
I'm scared you'll disappear...

492
00:29:46,449 --> 00:29:47,784
while I'm in Germany.

493
00:29:49,719 --> 00:29:51,621
You said it was a conference
you couldn't miss.

494
00:29:53,190 --> 00:29:55,292
Can you make me one promise?

495
00:29:56,693 --> 00:29:57,527
What?

496
00:29:57,961 --> 00:29:59,629
That no matter what happens,

497
00:30:01,298 --> 00:30:02,732
you won't leave me.

498
00:30:08,772 --> 00:30:10,707
You're thinking
about those two people again.

499
00:30:12,843 --> 00:30:16,012
To you, they're like family.

500
00:30:16,012 --> 00:30:16,847
And to me...

501
00:30:16,847 --> 00:30:18,081
Just tell me that.

502
00:30:19,115 --> 00:30:21,084
That no matter what happens,

503
00:30:23,153 --> 00:30:24,588
you won't leave me.

504
00:30:29,793 --> 00:30:31,862
Whenever I ask you something like this,

505
00:30:32,829 --> 00:30:34,130
you're always the same.

506
00:30:35,131 --> 00:30:37,901
I still haven't heard the answer I want.

507
00:30:38,368 --> 00:30:40,103
I'm right here beside you.

508
00:30:41,238 --> 00:30:42,472
I'm not going anywhere.

509
00:30:42,672 --> 00:30:43,707
I still...

510
00:30:46,243 --> 00:30:47,511
haven't heard you say...

511
00:30:48,078 --> 00:30:49,813
you love me even once.

512
00:30:50,614 --> 00:30:51,581
If...

513
00:30:53,984 --> 00:30:57,621
only the two of us were left...

514
00:31:05,095 --> 00:31:06,163
That will happen.

515
00:31:06,997 --> 00:31:07,898
I'm sure of it.

516
00:31:10,100 --> 00:31:10,967
Hee Su.

517
00:31:13,170 --> 00:31:14,471
Tomorrow is her birthday.

518
00:31:16,840 --> 00:31:20,010
When it's just the two of us,
I want us to talk about us.

519
00:31:20,911 --> 00:31:21,711
But...

520
00:31:21,711 --> 00:31:24,047
Chairman Choi returned
to Korea last night.

521
00:31:24,781 --> 00:31:26,383
The two of them will be together now.

522
00:31:27,484 --> 00:31:28,518
Don't worry.

523
00:31:29,986 --> 00:31:30,987
I see.

524
00:32:04,588 --> 00:32:06,356
- Enjoy your meal.
- Thank you.

525
00:32:10,160 --> 00:32:10,994
Myo Jin.

526
00:32:12,095 --> 00:32:12,863
Sorry.

527
00:32:21,304 --> 00:32:23,273
Chairman Choi Young Ho is back in Korea.

528
00:32:24,207 --> 00:32:25,041
Are you sure?

529
00:32:26,109 --> 00:32:27,844
Tomorrow is Hee Su's birthday,

530
00:32:27,844 --> 00:32:29,212
and he couldn't be with her last year,

531
00:32:29,212 --> 00:32:30,981
so he said he would
definitely come this year.

532
00:32:31,515 --> 00:32:33,216
Ryu Jun Ho said the same thing.

533
00:32:33,450 --> 00:32:34,618
It should be right.

534
00:32:34,618 --> 00:32:35,819
The chance has come.

535
00:32:35,819 --> 00:32:37,654
Ryu Jun Ho went to Germany this morning...

536
00:32:37,654 --> 00:32:39,055
for the conference.

537
00:32:39,890 --> 00:32:42,159
At the Jebu-do villa right now,
there should only be...

538
00:32:42,159 --> 00:32:43,360
Choi Young Ho and Choi Hee Su.

539
00:32:43,827 --> 00:32:45,295
This is a once-in-a-lifetime opportunity.

540
00:32:46,530 --> 00:32:47,864
How can I help?

541
00:32:53,870 --> 00:32:54,704
No.

542
00:32:55,505 --> 00:32:57,207
From here on, I'll handle it myself.

543
00:32:57,440 --> 00:32:58,842
Don't rush.

544
00:32:59,509 --> 00:33:00,944
They're not easy people.

545
00:33:02,612 --> 00:33:03,914
I'm ready.

546
00:33:04,915 --> 00:33:05,982
If I can kill...

547
00:33:06,983 --> 00:33:09,519
Choi Young Ho with my own hands,

548
00:33:10,387 --> 00:33:12,055
I don't care what happens to me.

549
00:33:12,823 --> 00:33:15,158
Don't rush. Take it slow.

550
00:33:16,393 --> 00:33:18,061
You said that to me once.

551
00:33:18,061 --> 00:33:19,029
Don't forget it.

552
00:33:32,342 --> 00:33:33,243
Hello?

553
00:33:33,543 --> 00:33:34,444
It's me.

554
00:33:35,779 --> 00:33:36,847
Jun Ho?

555
00:33:36,847 --> 00:33:37,681
Yeah.

556
00:33:38,715 --> 00:33:40,116
Have you already arrived?

557
00:33:40,383 --> 00:33:42,953
No. Chief Kim went to Germany in my place.

558
00:33:44,888 --> 00:33:47,157
How can someone else
attend the conference for you?

559
00:33:47,724 --> 00:33:49,226
I explained it well, so it's fine.

560
00:33:50,393 --> 00:33:52,596
I came to Japan for something urgent.

561
00:33:55,398 --> 00:33:57,501
I'll take care of some work and meet you,
even if it's late tonight.

562
00:33:57,868 --> 00:34:00,303
Around what time today?

563
00:34:00,937 --> 00:34:01,905
Late.

564
00:34:03,473 --> 00:34:05,041
I'll call you back on this number.

565
00:34:18,054 --> 00:34:20,957
The phone you have called is turned off.
After the beep...

566
00:34:32,102 --> 00:34:35,939
(The day of the accident)

567
00:35:44,040 --> 00:35:46,843
(LPG)

568
00:37:13,597 --> 00:37:14,764
Look who's here.

569
00:37:15,665 --> 00:37:16,600
Ham Myo Jin.

570
00:37:17,534 --> 00:37:19,169
You came all the way here?

571
00:37:20,470 --> 00:37:21,438
It's been a while.

572
00:37:38,054 --> 00:37:40,190
I know you didn't come
because you missed me.

573
00:37:41,224 --> 00:37:42,092
So why?

574
00:37:42,425 --> 00:37:44,161
Did you suddenly have something to ask?

575
00:37:49,199 --> 00:37:51,902
Or did you come to laugh at me?

576
00:37:52,202 --> 00:37:53,804
Sorry, but neither.

577
00:37:55,071 --> 00:37:56,873
I have nothing left to say to you.

578
00:37:56,873 --> 00:37:57,641
Really?

579
00:37:58,809 --> 00:38:00,010
I see.

580
00:38:04,648 --> 00:38:06,316
Are you trying to beat me to it?

581
00:38:07,050 --> 00:38:09,820
Do you think I still don't know
about you and Ryu Jun Ho?

582
00:38:10,453 --> 00:38:11,822
Think whatever you want.

583
00:38:13,456 --> 00:38:15,525
I'm not interested
in the two of you anymore.

584
00:38:16,960 --> 00:38:18,829
When did you grow up so much?

585
00:38:19,763 --> 00:38:20,997
My little Myo Jin.

586
00:38:24,601 --> 00:38:25,802
I'm not good at this kind of thing.

587
00:38:25,802 --> 00:38:27,504
Come on, pose for me.

588
00:38:28,071 --> 00:38:29,840
You saw what I did.

589
00:38:31,641 --> 00:38:32,742
They do stuff like this.

590
00:38:34,845 --> 00:38:36,213
Should I say...

591
00:38:36,847 --> 00:38:38,048
what you want to say first?

592
00:38:39,583 --> 00:38:41,852
If you like him that much, just take him.

593
00:38:43,186 --> 00:38:44,387
I'm sick of him now.

594
00:38:47,224 --> 00:38:48,792
I did think about...

595
00:38:49,793 --> 00:38:52,229
what I should do with the two of you.

596
00:38:54,831 --> 00:38:56,500
Should I let you two go...

597
00:38:57,300 --> 00:38:59,236
or keep you two tied down?

598
00:39:02,105 --> 00:39:04,007
I'm the one who always decides.

599
00:39:04,941 --> 00:39:06,610
You should know that much by now.

600
00:39:10,981 --> 00:39:11,948
Come on.

601
00:39:11,948 --> 00:39:13,717
Make a heart.

602
00:39:14,784 --> 00:39:16,186
Okay, act handsome.

603
00:39:16,186 --> 00:39:17,187
Act cool.

604
00:39:19,756 --> 00:39:21,124
You're so funny.

605
00:39:21,124 --> 00:39:22,692
Ryu Jun Ho, you're handsome.

606
00:39:25,562 --> 00:39:27,164
Do you know what my wish is?

607
00:39:27,164 --> 00:39:29,166
Come on, I want to take a picture.

608
00:39:29,166 --> 00:39:30,667
To go back to that day...

609
00:39:30,667 --> 00:39:31,434
Look here.

610
00:39:31,434 --> 00:39:33,303
and start everything over again,

611
00:39:34,070 --> 00:39:35,272
from the very beginning.

612
00:39:37,974 --> 00:39:39,042
Ryu Jun Ho...

613
00:39:41,545 --> 00:39:43,613
will never escape me
for the rest of his life.

614
00:39:46,683 --> 00:39:48,318
Without my permission,

615
00:39:48,618 --> 00:39:49,820
the two of you can't do anything.

616
00:39:52,823 --> 00:39:53,723
Do you know...

617
00:39:55,425 --> 00:39:57,194
what happened that day?

618
00:39:58,028 --> 00:39:59,629
The weather is so nice.

619
00:39:59,629 --> 00:40:00,630
Beautiful.

620
00:40:02,132 --> 00:40:03,633
Smile.

621
00:40:03,633 --> 00:40:04,634
I said smile.

622
00:40:06,837 --> 00:40:07,771
What?

623
00:40:08,405 --> 00:40:09,673
Why are you making that face?

624
00:40:10,307 --> 00:40:12,442
Anyone would think
you had some terminal illness.

625
00:40:18,615 --> 00:40:20,350
Even after seeing this,
does it still not feel real?

626
00:40:21,218 --> 00:40:23,553
We're really going to America now.

627
00:40:23,553 --> 00:40:25,155
You to Brown, me to RISD.

628
00:40:25,422 --> 00:40:26,356
Aren't you happy?

629
00:40:30,727 --> 00:40:32,462
Are you seriously
going to keep acting like this?

630
00:40:32,729 --> 00:40:34,231
Why are you so serious?

631
00:40:35,799 --> 00:40:38,235
I feel like I'm going abroad to study
by begging for it.

632
00:40:39,302 --> 00:40:41,104
Going this far to make it happen
just feels wrong.

633
00:40:41,104 --> 00:40:41,972
You fool.

634
00:40:42,806 --> 00:40:45,075
I told you I already talked to my dad.

635
00:40:45,075 --> 00:40:46,143
So what?

636
00:40:46,143 --> 00:40:48,211
Tuition and living expenses
are too much money.

637
00:40:48,678 --> 00:40:51,081
It'll keep costing this much for years.

638
00:40:51,081 --> 00:40:52,916
How can I owe him all of it?

639
00:40:52,916 --> 00:40:54,184
Get a part-time job there.

640
00:40:55,285 --> 00:40:57,387
Study hard and get a scholarship too.

641
00:40:57,821 --> 00:40:59,422
That's all. What are you worried about?

642
00:41:00,357 --> 00:41:02,325
I already did the math.

643
00:41:03,026 --> 00:41:05,395
It'll only be enough for me
to buy the books I want to read.

644
00:41:09,432 --> 00:41:10,267
You fool.

645
00:41:11,301 --> 00:41:12,502
Are you really going to do that?

646
00:41:13,236 --> 00:41:15,438
Do you think I'd just let you
struggle like that?

647
00:41:18,608 --> 00:41:20,076
Dad said so.

648
00:41:20,710 --> 00:41:22,179
You can pay him back later
once you succeed.

649
00:41:22,646 --> 00:41:24,014
Then it's fine.

650
00:41:24,014 --> 00:41:25,448
Even so...

651
00:41:25,448 --> 00:41:26,583
Be quiet.

652
00:41:27,784 --> 00:41:28,985
That means you should treat me well.

653
00:41:30,453 --> 00:41:31,321
Otherwise...

654
00:41:32,722 --> 00:41:33,723
Otherwise?

655
00:41:34,157 --> 00:41:36,226
You can go be an idiot and join the army.

656
00:41:40,163 --> 00:41:41,631
You'd better be good to me.

657
00:41:50,607 --> 00:41:51,475
Hey.

658
00:41:51,475 --> 00:41:52,909
Pull over, now.

659
00:41:53,276 --> 00:41:55,545
We drank. You're drunk right now.

660
00:41:55,846 --> 00:41:56,713
I don't want to.

661
00:41:56,980 --> 00:41:58,415
There's no one around.
What's the big deal?

662
00:41:58,615 --> 00:41:59,916
It's dangerous. Pull over.

663
00:41:59,916 --> 00:42:00,884
Stop the car!

664
00:42:01,251 --> 00:42:03,220
Why are you always so serious?

665
00:42:03,587 --> 00:42:05,355
You won't let me do anything fun.

666
00:42:05,355 --> 00:42:06,923
I'm not listening to you anymore.

667
00:42:09,593 --> 00:42:10,660
Stop acting crazy.

668
00:42:10,660 --> 00:42:11,895
Stop right now!

669
00:42:12,162 --> 00:42:13,063
No.

670
00:42:13,330 --> 00:42:15,365
Who would be out here
in this backwater place?

671
00:42:15,365 --> 00:42:16,233
Let go.

672
00:42:16,967 --> 00:42:17,968
It's my choice.

673
00:42:19,903 --> 00:42:21,138
Please, stop it.

674
00:42:24,174 --> 00:42:25,609
The cherry blossoms are so beautiful.

675
00:42:29,045 --> 00:42:30,013
No!

676
00:42:42,292 --> 00:42:44,127
What if she finds out it died?

677
00:42:45,395 --> 00:42:46,763
Myo Jin...

678
00:42:47,664 --> 00:42:49,666
will cry her eyes out.

679
00:42:50,300 --> 00:42:52,536
I'm so upset.

680
00:42:55,605 --> 00:42:58,208
What are you going to do
about the crack in your arm?

681
00:42:58,408 --> 00:43:00,544
Forget it. It's nothing.

682
00:43:00,777 --> 00:43:02,979
What do you mean, nothing?

683
00:43:02,979 --> 00:43:04,347
I was really shocked.

684
00:43:05,148 --> 00:43:08,084
In this day and age,
how can young people still drive drunk?

685
00:43:09,586 --> 00:43:10,520
So?

686
00:43:11,655 --> 00:43:12,889
What did those kids say?

687
00:43:15,058 --> 00:43:16,960
They brought up money first.

688
00:43:16,960 --> 00:43:18,728
They said they'd pay whatever I asked,

689
00:43:18,728 --> 00:43:20,497
as long as I didn't report them.

690
00:43:22,699 --> 00:43:26,736
Young kids like that, with that mindset...

691
00:43:28,572 --> 00:43:30,173
Then what about our dog?

692
00:43:31,208 --> 00:43:33,643
What did they say about killing our dog?

693
00:43:34,945 --> 00:43:36,847
If they don't even care
that a person got hurt,

694
00:43:36,847 --> 00:43:38,982
do you think they care about a mere dog?

695
00:43:39,816 --> 00:43:41,518
What nasty little brats.

696
00:43:42,252 --> 00:43:43,787
Before they cause an even bigger accident,

697
00:43:43,787 --> 00:43:45,655
shouldn't someone teach them a lesson?

698
00:43:45,655 --> 00:43:46,523
Yes.

699
00:43:47,090 --> 00:43:49,392
I told them
I was reporting them to the police,

700
00:43:49,392 --> 00:43:51,461
so they'd better be ready.

701
00:43:51,795 --> 00:43:54,164
I said they should go to jail
and learn their lesson.

702
00:43:54,698 --> 00:43:56,900
I took photos of everything on my phone.

703
00:44:07,310 --> 00:44:10,247
They say drunk-driving laws
are really strict these days.

704
00:44:11,681 --> 00:44:13,116
Isn't that a bit too far?

705
00:44:14,551 --> 00:44:17,354
Ruining young kids' futures is too...

706
00:44:20,957 --> 00:44:22,659
I know.

707
00:44:22,659 --> 00:44:23,994
I won't call the police.

708
00:44:24,327 --> 00:44:26,029
I didn't even report them.

709
00:44:27,597 --> 00:44:30,000
But those kids...

710
00:45:13,176 --> 00:45:14,077
Hee Su.

711
00:45:14,344 --> 00:45:15,645
It's all because of you.

712
00:45:15,645 --> 00:45:16,746
Get out of my sight.

713
00:45:16,746 --> 00:45:18,615
Disappear from my sight.

714
00:45:18,615 --> 00:45:19,716
You and I...

715
00:45:20,050 --> 00:45:21,518
were driving drunk without licenses.

716
00:45:21,852 --> 00:45:23,720
Forget studying in America. It's all over.

717
00:45:24,187 --> 00:45:26,056
My life is over!

718
00:45:31,595 --> 00:45:32,929
Dad is going to kill me.

719
00:45:33,430 --> 00:45:34,464
Hey.

720
00:45:34,464 --> 00:45:35,832
What are you going to tell my dad?

721
00:45:38,969 --> 00:45:40,937
What am I supposed to do
if you just do nothing like that?

722
00:45:41,304 --> 00:45:42,973
Are you not thinking at all right now?

723
00:45:42,973 --> 00:45:44,307
Are you insane?

724
00:45:44,541 --> 00:45:46,543
What about your promise to my dad?

725
00:45:47,043 --> 00:45:50,013
You did this to me,
and you have nothing to say?

726
00:45:50,480 --> 00:45:51,781
I'll figure something out.

727
00:45:52,616 --> 00:45:53,450
Shut up.

728
00:45:55,385 --> 00:45:56,786
He filmed everything...

729
00:45:57,287 --> 00:45:58,788
and took the liquor bottles
with our fingerprints on them...

730
00:45:58,788 --> 00:46:00,056
to hand over to the police.

731
00:46:00,457 --> 00:46:01,925
I refused to go to the police station,

732
00:46:01,925 --> 00:46:03,527
so we only barely avoided
being dragged there.

733
00:46:03,527 --> 00:46:04,427
Hey.

734
00:46:04,427 --> 00:46:06,530
Why the hell did you admit that I drank?

735
00:46:07,697 --> 00:46:08,498
Why?

736
00:46:08,999 --> 00:46:10,367
After you did
every stupid thing you could,

737
00:46:10,367 --> 00:46:12,269
what are you going to do now?

738
00:46:32,756 --> 00:46:33,690
I know.

739
00:46:37,227 --> 00:46:39,229
This is something I should handle.

740
00:46:41,364 --> 00:46:43,667
I promised your father
I'd take care of you.

741
00:46:47,971 --> 00:46:49,105
I'll handle it myself.

742
00:46:51,975 --> 00:46:53,577
That's what I'm here for.

743
00:46:58,181 --> 00:46:59,616
If it's for you, I should do it.

744
00:47:01,918 --> 00:47:03,053
That's how it should be.

745
00:47:13,864 --> 00:47:15,732
It was such a perfect day.

746
00:47:17,968 --> 00:47:19,769
That day was my birthday,

747
00:47:20,170 --> 00:47:21,071
and the day before,

748
00:47:22,873 --> 00:47:24,774
the acceptance letters came from America,

749
00:47:25,075 --> 00:47:26,376
for both of us.

750
00:47:44,861 --> 00:47:45,695
Hello?

751
00:48:10,687 --> 00:48:11,621
What should I do?

752
00:48:13,790 --> 00:48:14,791
Was it...

753
00:48:16,860 --> 00:48:17,994
you two?

754
00:48:20,764 --> 00:48:21,598
What?

755
00:48:22,766 --> 00:48:24,301
Did Ryu Jun Ho tell you?

756
00:48:25,535 --> 00:48:26,403
Tell me.

757
00:48:28,104 --> 00:48:29,105
Was it you two?

758
00:48:29,105 --> 00:48:30,540
Did he tell you that?

759
00:48:32,809 --> 00:48:34,411
That crazy bastard.

760
00:48:36,446 --> 00:48:38,014
The one who set the fire was Ryu Jun Ho.

761
00:48:38,648 --> 00:48:40,684
Ryu Jun Ho killed those people.

762
00:48:44,221 --> 00:48:45,121
Why?

763
00:48:46,389 --> 00:48:47,324
For what reason?

764
00:48:47,324 --> 00:48:48,692
Are you really asking me that?

765
00:48:48,692 --> 00:48:50,126
Imagine if this got out.

766
00:48:50,126 --> 00:48:51,761
People would all blame me.

767
00:48:52,529 --> 00:48:54,598
They wouldn't even know
what really happened,

768
00:48:54,598 --> 00:48:56,766
but they'd all go crazy
trying to tear me apart.

769
00:49:00,370 --> 00:49:02,372
It wasn't something
that had to get that big.

770
00:49:05,142 --> 00:49:06,643
Yes, we caused the accident,

771
00:49:07,177 --> 00:49:08,745
but we admitted our mistake...

772
00:49:09,112 --> 00:49:12,249
and said we'd compensate him fully,
as much as he wanted.

773
00:49:12,249 --> 00:49:14,651
But he kept threatening
to put us in prison.

774
00:49:15,619 --> 00:49:16,686
Is that...

775
00:49:19,122 --> 00:49:20,991
the reason...

776
00:49:22,959 --> 00:49:23,894
you killed people?

777
00:49:26,429 --> 00:49:28,331
They weren't people...

778
00:49:30,667 --> 00:49:32,068
who deserved...

779
00:49:33,103 --> 00:49:33,937
to die like that.

780
00:49:50,620 --> 00:49:51,621
I told you.

781
00:49:53,690 --> 00:49:54,825
From that moment on,

782
00:49:57,360 --> 00:49:59,196
I had a reason it had to be that way.

783
00:50:00,831 --> 00:50:02,132
Now you understand too, don't you?

784
00:50:03,500 --> 00:50:04,468
How I felt.

785
00:50:05,936 --> 00:50:07,270
Do you understand my pain?

786
00:50:07,270 --> 00:50:08,371
That was your reason...

787
00:50:09,973 --> 00:50:11,441
for killing those people?

788
00:50:11,441 --> 00:50:12,676
I told you.

789
00:50:12,943 --> 00:50:15,479
Back then, we got acceptance letters
from the best universities in America.

790
00:50:15,479 --> 00:50:16,379
Can that...

791
00:50:18,281 --> 00:50:20,484
be a reason to kill people?

792
00:50:25,422 --> 00:50:27,357
People with nothing to lose...

793
00:50:28,191 --> 00:50:30,694
all think like you, of course.

794
00:50:32,062 --> 00:50:32,929
What?

795
00:50:35,065 --> 00:50:35,832
You.

796
00:50:36,333 --> 00:50:38,702
When you first came to my exhibition
and saw my paintings, you cried.

797
00:50:39,536 --> 00:50:40,637
You said it yourself...

798
00:50:41,471 --> 00:50:43,306
that you could feel
my sorrow inside my paintings.

799
00:50:43,673 --> 00:50:44,574
My passion,

800
00:50:45,208 --> 00:50:47,477
my talent, all of it, so vividly.

801
00:50:48,044 --> 00:50:50,046
You said that you'd never felt
anything like it before.

802
00:50:51,448 --> 00:50:52,682
You're insane.

803
00:50:54,050 --> 00:50:56,353
If those people had ruined me back then,

804
00:51:02,692 --> 00:51:03,860
my paintings...

805
00:51:06,263 --> 00:51:07,864
wouldn't exist in the world now.

806
00:51:11,601 --> 00:51:13,103
Can you even imagine that?

807
00:51:19,943 --> 00:51:20,877
Hey.

808
00:51:21,111 --> 00:51:23,814
Do you know
what people with nothing to lose...

809
00:51:25,382 --> 00:51:27,150
are capable of?

810
00:51:31,822 --> 00:51:32,856
They only wait for their chance.

811
00:51:33,456 --> 00:51:36,026
They wait to find fault
with people who have money,

812
00:51:36,359 --> 00:51:38,295
and when they get the chance,
they pounce and rip them apart.

813
00:51:38,295 --> 00:51:39,162
Like animals.

814
00:51:40,096 --> 00:51:41,865
That's what happened to us that day.

815
00:51:42,766 --> 00:51:44,901
There is no one in this world
who has nothing to lose.

816
00:51:45,869 --> 00:51:48,505
Because those people were
someone's father and someone's mother too.

817
00:53:15,492 --> 00:53:16,827
Honey.

818
00:53:17,961 --> 00:53:19,663
Honey, what do we do?

819
00:53:19,663 --> 00:53:21,031
It's a fire. Wait.

820
00:53:22,566 --> 00:53:23,467
Honey.

821
00:53:23,467 --> 00:53:25,001
Wait a second.

822
00:53:30,407 --> 00:53:31,241
No.

823
00:53:37,380 --> 00:53:38,215
Mom.

824
00:53:38,748 --> 00:53:40,116
Mom, Dad.

825
00:53:43,353 --> 00:53:45,689
- Myo Jin.
- Mom.

826
00:53:45,689 --> 00:53:46,590
Myo Jin.

827
00:53:46,590 --> 00:53:47,524
Mom.

828
00:53:48,325 --> 00:53:49,192
Myo Jin.

829
00:53:51,962 --> 00:53:52,996
Honey.

830
00:53:53,663 --> 00:53:55,432
Mom.

831
00:53:56,700 --> 00:53:57,567
Mom.

832
00:53:59,769 --> 00:54:01,204
Mom, no.

833
00:54:01,204 --> 00:54:02,606
No.

834
00:54:03,874 --> 00:54:05,075
No, Mom.

835
00:54:05,075 --> 00:54:06,776
Myo Jin, get out quickly.

836
00:54:06,776 --> 00:54:09,212
I'll get your mom out. Go.

837
00:54:09,212 --> 00:54:10,347
- Go.
- Hurry, go.

838
00:54:10,347 --> 00:54:12,115
Go, Myo Jin.

839
00:54:12,115 --> 00:54:13,283
No.

840
00:54:13,283 --> 00:54:15,485
I can't go.

841
00:54:15,485 --> 00:54:17,320
Go, Myo Jin.

842
00:54:17,320 --> 00:54:18,788
No.

843
00:54:23,193 --> 00:54:24,694
What is happening?

844
00:54:26,897 --> 00:54:27,898
Mom, Dad.

845
00:54:27,898 --> 00:54:29,266
Mom, Dad, no.

846
00:54:29,266 --> 00:54:31,034
Mom, Dad.

847
00:54:31,501 --> 00:54:33,203
Why won't this work? Get up.

848
00:54:33,203 --> 00:54:34,237
Dad, no.

849
00:54:34,237 --> 00:54:35,238
No.

850
00:54:35,238 --> 00:54:36,807
No, Mom.

851
00:54:36,807 --> 00:54:37,808
Dad.

852
00:54:39,676 --> 00:54:40,944
Myo Jin.

853
00:54:40,944 --> 00:54:42,512
Myo Jin!

854
00:54:45,916 --> 00:54:46,883
Myo Jin.

855
00:54:47,584 --> 00:54:48,852
If you go in there, you'll die.

856
00:54:48,852 --> 00:54:50,654
- Dad.
- You'll die too.

857
00:54:50,654 --> 00:54:52,656
Mom, Dad.

858
00:54:54,124 --> 00:54:55,192
Dad.

859
00:55:01,131 --> 00:55:02,098
No.

860
00:55:02,332 --> 00:55:03,366
No.

861
00:55:03,700 --> 00:55:05,068
No.

862
00:55:05,068 --> 00:55:06,069
No!

863
00:55:42,539 --> 00:55:47,110
(REVERSE)

864
00:55:47,410 --> 00:55:49,346
Choi Hee Su and Ryu Jun Ho.

865
00:55:49,346 --> 00:55:50,981
I'm sure it isn't a coincidence.

866
00:55:50,981 --> 00:55:53,550
Because there's no such thing
as revenge that only gives back...

867
00:55:53,550 --> 00:55:54,885
what was done to you.

868
00:55:54,885 --> 00:55:56,553
Should I give that present to you?

869
00:55:56,887 --> 00:55:59,456
You have to remember.

870
00:56:00,056 --> 00:56:01,725
Over one stupid memory?

871
00:56:01,725 --> 00:56:03,960
It's already over and gone.

872
00:56:03,960 --> 00:56:06,263
You went all the way to the villa
to save Choi Hee Su...

873
00:56:06,563 --> 00:56:08,131
and almost lost your life.

874
00:56:08,465 --> 00:56:11,201
But my feelings remembered you,

875
00:56:11,501 --> 00:56:13,436
and they showed me what I had to do.

876
00:56:14,304 --> 00:56:16,306
